cafes.name: Constellation Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 3320 E Lake Lansing Rd, East Lansing, MI 48823, USA

text.text: Our kids love to visit the cat cafe. Helps the sweet cats find homes and is such a calm thing to do for an hour. Excited to see their new location when it‚Äôs ready!

Laid back place! I had an everything bagel & maple iced coffee with sweet foam! Super good! I loved all the cats and got to see so many different cat personalities, breeds, sizes and ages!!! If you‚Äôre obsessed with cats and want a coffee and a  decompressing place - go here!!!!! I‚Äôd rate 10/10 stars if I could! Also super cute gift shop area!

Constellation Cat Cafe is a place I recommend people go to if you adore cats & love sweet drinks! The cats there are all well socialized and friendly. The environment has a very cute aesthetic. The place is extremely well taken care of. The staff makes sure to clean everything thoroughly. They keep the cats and the coffee area separated for food safety. All the cats are well taken care of and provided with so many areas to play & rest at. Super easy to lose track of time here with how peaceful it is. There are plenty of tables and chairs to sit at, even some couches. By the front entrance, there‚Äôs a bunch of art you‚Äôre able to purchase for example stickers, bags, shirts, water bottles, and so on.

This place is just so incredible!! Everything from the drinks to the cats to the people are just amazing and so welcoming. They have the best popping boba drinks I've ever had, and the kitties are so sweet and friendly! üêàThe woman working here is very kind and thoughtful, and she immediately made me and my entire family feel safe and welcomed. This cat cafe is really a must visit!! ‚ô•Ô∏è‚ô•Ô∏è‚ô•Ô∏è

I've come here as a customer and as a volunteer multiple times, and I have never been let down by Crystal and her staff/other volunteers. They're all so kind and ready help, even when I showed up to volunteer having no experience and not knowing what to do. Some of my family even adopted a cat from here, and the lengths Crystal went through to ensure Alaska (the cat :]) went to a good home was phenomenal. I only wish I could be of more help, honestly. The place is always clean, and I like to help preserve that with volunteering, but nonetheless it's always a beautiful place to walk into. If I could rate this place a million stars I would. Love you Cozy Cats üíñ

Edit: Crystal if you see this, this is Skyler. Didn't realize I was posting using this account LOL.

This place is HEAVEN!!!!! My partner and I went to hang out with the cats because my mother is allergic and we can't have a furry friend of our own right now!!! This is the perfect place for people either who can't bring a cat home but still adore them, or if you're looking to adopt!!!! Our favorite was Panda, they 5 year old tuxedo he was very calm and chill. and a black kitten named Pantera, he was so playful and sweet!! Cookie Monster, the white and mixed tabby, was also so sweet as well. We will definetley be back for more playtime with the sweet fluff balls :)))

It was a fun experience. The volunteers were very polite and told us which 3 cats we shouldn‚Äôt touch and the cats were on top of the cages. We went at 4 pm and the cats didn‚Äôt start warming up to us until a half hour or so. They were so cute. There was a total of 25 cats. A lot of them were sleeping or didn‚Äôt want to be bothered. The concept is cool. It definitely nice experience to hangout with cats for an hour. A total of 15 people can be in at time. I made an appointment online. There‚Äôs coffee and baked goods you can have and two restrooms in the waiting area.

I have been a volunteer here for almost 5 years.  They are a wonderful community resource and rescue for our feline friends.  If you haven‚Äôt visited before now is the time!  Whether it is just to hang out with cats, adopt a furry friend, foster or volunteer you can‚Äôt go wrong with the Ferndale Cat Shelter and Catf√© !

!!!I was given sick cats to foster to adopt!!!
!!!I was not told they were sick until pickup!!!

I went through an emotional rollercoaster trying to adopt from this catfe

I went multiple times to visit the cats, spending money every time. Then once I found 2 cats I loved I moved to foster to adopt. I was set to foster to adopt about a month out, starting December 30th.

Long story short - I was given sick cats, and I wasn't told they were sick until I picked them up. I was given medicine, and I treated them as needed for two weeks until January 12th. After two weeks the ringworm from one cat transferred to another. I could tell this because the hair was missing on her ear.

I reached out for help because I was not told that I would be given sick cats.

I was then told that if I do not take care of the sick cats, I will not be able to adopt them.

This was the craziest experience I've ever gone through. They were very unorganized, and thought that I adopted the cats. I found this out once they had me sign surrender papers, which confused me.

If you do adopt from this catfe I suggest fostering to adopt to ensure that you aren't given sick cats.

Unknown City.name: Black Cat Beanery
Unknown City.address: 1192 S Lapeer Rd, Orion Twp, MI 48360, USA

text.text:
bcb is such an amazing place to go and this is your sign to visit if you‚Äôve never been!

i‚Äôve been coming here regularly for about two months now, and it‚Äôs so clear how much the staff cares about these sweet cats, and how well taken care of they are. the staff (made of mostly volunteers) are always willing to answer any questions you might have - and the owners are clearly super passionate and care about these cats and getting them into new homes! unlike other cat cafes, this one doesn‚Äôt smell, the cats have super distinct personalities, AND they have adult-only wednesday nights (highly recommend if u like dim lighting, seeing sleepy kitties, and avoiding loud noises). overall, bcb is amazing, they‚Äôre constantly rotating new cats in as the current ones get adopted to their new homes, so there‚Äôs always someone new to see, and they‚Äôre constantly offering activities with the kitties as well, so there‚Äôs always something new to do!

BTW you can sponsor a cat for $25 a month if you don‚Äôt have the means to adopt - shout out my boy pogo!

TLDR: bcb rules - go visit them asap and pet brock for me!!

I can't say enough good things about this place! The setup is really well done - lots of toys and cool fixtures for the cats, plenty of places to sit (for humans and cats alike), and a variety of ways to interact. The cats are largely social and playful with lots of options for them to be admired from afar when they need a break. We had my daughter's tenth birthday here and one of her friends commented on how many cats get adopted and then a shelter kitty takes its place. She said, "So when you adopt a cat from here, it's like you're really saving two."

My family and I had a great time at the Black Cat Beanery today. The cats provide endless entertainment and have so many different toys, ledges, and items to explore while you interact with them. They had 15 available cats today in a super clean and fun environment. It is different than we expected because the snacks/drinks are in a separate area due to health code reasons but  you come for the STARS - all the cats.  Check it out and help the great organization finding homes for cats - they‚Äôre up to almost 100 adopted as of today.

cafes.name: Happy Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 447 Division Ave S, Grand Rapids, MI 49503, USA

text.text: This is genuinely one of the coolest places I've ever visited! The cats were so friendly and sweet. The barista was super friendly when she was answering my questions. The cats were very well cared for and they had plenty of spaces to curl up in when they didn't want to hang out with people. The latte I got was so good! It had amazing flavor and was exactly as described on the menu! I would definitely recommend coming here if you love cats! üê±üêà

I love it here! I've been a few times over the years, I came back again last week. The kitties are so cute! Ray is a sweetheart, love that furry fella. Everytime I went, I had a great time playing with the kitties. I always get hot chocolate when I go here, so yummy! Lovely experience, I'd recommend this to anyone who loves kitties nearly as much as I do

Everything cats and also some coffee.

IMPORTANT: Entrance is in the back (west side of the building).

- Cotton Kitty - $6.50: A VERY flavor-filled juice and pop mixed beverage.  The cotton candy taste is not too dominant, but is a great balance.  The lemon and Sprite is a bit more of a nuance.  It has a bit of a kick with something, but I could not place it.  My daughter was super thrilled with the sparkles (I did not get a picture, sorry).

They do serve hot chocolate and white chocolate mocha.  They have other drinks including Red Bull, Izze, Mott‚Äôs apple juice, Faygo, Moon Mist, Sprite, Coca-Cola, Diet, bottled water, and more.  They also have nuts, chocolate candies, chips, muffins, edible straws, candy, soup, and more.  Looks like they‚Äôve expanded a lot of their stock over their existence.

There are tables and chairs to sit at in the cafe as well as in the cat room.

- Service: Super friendly and cheerful.  Answered all our questions.

- Atmosphere: Everything cats!  What do you expect?  They have cat gear including collars, dishes, catnip, medicines, health, toys, collar bandanas, carriers, tents/caves, and so much more.  They also have books, games, stuffed animals, mugs, keychains, towels, socks, birthday cards, shirts,bags, stickers, and anything they can find with cats.  You‚Äôll find common cat themes like Hello Kitty as well.  There is plenty of cat artwork, too.

The cafe and shop is open anytime without reservation, but the cat room is by reservation only, though if they are not busy, they can still get you in.  The cat room is separate from the cafe and shop.  You enter through a small staging room (you are supposed to use hand sanitizer here before and after).  A lot of people were bringing their drinks into the room.

We did not enter, but watched through the big picture window.  The cats seemed to be overly stimulated and not interested in playing much when we were there, but there were a LOT of people trying to interact with them.  None of them seemed grumpy or aggressive, though.  Just lazy.  Again, weekdays will probably be best.

They have helped facilitate the adoption of almost a thousand cats (937 according to the bead jar pictured).  We saw between five and seven cats when looking in.  I‚Äôm guessing there are probably more hiding, though.

Also, follow the posted rules.  This includes being sanitary, keep kids supervised, only pick up cats when seated (and stay seated), avoid sudden movements and noises, read body language of cats, don‚Äôt reach into tunnels (they can bite), no human food/drinks for cats, only staff can access storage, etc.

- Conclusion: It‚Äôs a total cat place.  If that is your thing, you will dig this place hook, line, and sinker for sure.

If you are interested in adopting, visit on a weekday.  If you come on a weekend, expect to make a reservation.

Visited on a Saturday at 3pm.

cafes.name: Malu Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 29552 Ford Rd, Garden City, MI 48135, USA

text.text: Loads of fun playing and snuggling with all the different cats. They were all friendly. They loved the spoon fed treats, so I would recommend grabbing a couple of those. The coffee was really good as well!

We went to Malu Cat Cafe for the first time today and had a great time! I don‚Äôt understand all of the bad reviews. Me and my two young boys went. The cats were healthy and seemed happy and well cared for. There were not any areas ‚Äúblocked off‚Äù to them. They were not shaking or hiding. They all seemed very well adjusted. When we first arrived all but one cat was sleeping. A little kitten followed us around and was very friendly and playful. After 15 minutes a lot of the cats started to wake up. Some wandered around and let visitors pet and play with them. There were several kittens that were very active and friendly. The cafe and cat area was clean. There were toys and brushes for the cats. Some reviews said the cats acted like they had been starving when given treats. I have had cats my whole life. Most cats love treats and devour them. I found no evidence of any mistreatment or stress in the cats. If I did I would e the first to report it. Many of the cats were available for adoption. This is a wonderful place and we can‚Äôt wait to return!

Just came here for my Aunt‚Äôs birthday. Expectations completely exceeded. The staff were lovely. They even brought us our drinks while we were all enamored with the kitties. Not expensive at all. They have a great variety of cats, most of which are very social! The kitties that were sleeping were just peacefully snoozing away. A few cats even came to sit on my lap. They look healthy with the softest of coats. Absolutely would recommend and come here again. They have a great thing going here! ü´∂üèª

cafes.name: Avocato Catf√© and Adoption Center
cafes.address: 38437 Grand River Ave, Farmington Hills, MI 48335, USA

text.text: Had an amazing experience at the Avocato Catf√©! While we didn‚Äôt get food or drinks I enjoyed an amazing time just chilling with cats. The kittens had their own room where they could play while the adult cats roamed, choosing who to play or get pets from. Volunteers were kind and very informative, helping individuals and families even when there were technical difficulties. Look forward to going again.
I had a great time the staff and volunteers were very friendly. The set up is nice and cozy for both the visitors and the cats. I know where I will be adopting my cat(s) from in the near future.

Fabulous, fun, and clean cat cafe! All of the cats seem very happy and comfortable in the environment and it's a great place to spend time with adoptable kitties. There's even a kitten room with several adorable kittens who run around and play like crazy - they're so fun to watch!

There's many vegan snacks available to purchase and a great selection of coffees and teas to enjoy while visiting with the cats.  I highly recommend visiting Avocato Catfe and supporting this wonderful organization. It's a great place to adopt a cat and/ or kitten, as well if you're looking!

cafes.name: Kzoo Cat Cafe and Rescue
cafes.address: 4221 S Westnedge Ave, Kalamazoo, MI 49008, USA

text.text:
I recently visited the Cat Cafe, and overall, we had a great time! It's important to note (for those who have never been) that this isn't a cafe in the traditional sense‚Äîthere's no freshly prepared food, just prepackaged and sealed snacks. This wasn't an issue for us since we mainly came to enjoy the company of the cats, and in that regard, the cafe did not disappoint. The cats were friendly, playful, and clearly well cared for, making our visit a delightful experience.

However, one hiccup we encountered was a last-minute request to change our appointment time due to overbooking. While this worked out fine for us, I can see how it could be inconvenient for others who may have stricter schedules.

Despite this minor issue, we enjoyed our time there and would recommend it to any cat lover looking for a cozy place to unwind and spend time with some adorable felines.

Lovely staff and lovely kitties, only down side was that our appointment ended up being with some younger kids who stole toys I was using out of my hand because a cat they wanted to play with was with me and when a cat sat on my lap they got excited and started getting in the kitties face with a toy making him run off and even one time wrapping a slinky around a cat's neck when it was sleeping and the parents did not seem to say anything to their behavior. Of course I understand that other people are also there to play with the kitties but it was unfortunate that when a cat would start becoming friendly with me, a kid would come and take my toy to play with the cat I was instead of the other cats who were also awake and playful. Otherwise, the cats and staff were very nice and I loved getting to play with QTip and Sardine and hope to come back.

I cannot express to you what a wonderful experience I had at the Kzoo Cat Cafe.  It was the best $15 I have spent all year!  Kitties glore to lavish attention on!  It will be the best $15 you have spent in a LONG time!  Simply heartwarming!

cafes.name: The Catz Den with Country Cat Lady
cafes.address: 120 S Main St, Wayland, MI 49348, USA

text.text: This place is amazing! Beautiful area, donate and cuddle some extremely sweet kitties, what more could you want!?
We a pair of litter mates, Maisie and Blue Moon, from the Country Cat Lady.  She choose the pair based on what she saw in my wife and me. Great match!  They came nurtured, spade and house broken.

Nestled in Waylands community lies The Catz Den, a haven of warmth and camaraderie where guests are greeted with open arms and the gentle purring of feline companions. From petting cats for a suggested donation to crafting, snacking, and playing games, every moment at The Catz Den is filled with joy and connection. It's a place where guests feel not just welcome but cherished, leaving with hearts full of gratitude and memories to treasure. For those seeking solace, companionship, and the gentle embrace of whiskered friends, The Catz Den is an absolute must-visit.

cafes.name: Three Cats [at Leon & Lulu]
cafes.address: 116 W 14 Mile Rd, Clawson, MI 48017, USA

text.text:
My family hails from Virginia, but we're currently enjoying some time in Detroit! We had planned to check out another restaurant, but when we saw the long line and how cramped it was, we decided to switch things up. Our family of four was getting pretty hangry, so I quickly searched for nearby food and, to our surprise, discovered an even better spot!

Three Cats is such a unique place! It's a transformed old movie theater that beautifully combines mid-century modern design with eclectic charm. From the fun, hand-stamped menus to the stunning logo that cleverly uses negative space, everything about it was just delightful. The atmosphere was so inviting!

As someone with a mobility disability, I really appreciated how kind and accommodating everyone was. To my surprise, the entire space was wheelchair accessible! There was plenty of room between tables, and it was easy to move around with a walker or have a service animal curl up beside us. The staff was wonderfully respectful of my family's various needs, ensuring everyone felt welcome and well taken care of.

Our waitress, SJ (Sarah Jane), was an absolute gem! I can't recommend her enough! Her passion for the menu and the genuine excitement she brought to our discussions about the food, ambiance, and service made our experience even better. She was so knowledgeable, sharing backstories and giving us a behind-the-scenes look at how the dishes were prepared. Plus, she had fantastic recommendations when we were having trouble deciding what to order.

Some of our favorite dishes included the mushroom soup, quiche, double chocolate muffin, chicken and waffles, and the delightful cattail mocktails called The Nancy Drew. Everything was just fabulous!
We didn‚Äôt have a reservation,  it they were very accommodating. We got a great seat by the bar and the food was excellent. Everyone was so friendly. Definitely recommend this brunch spot.

Came here for brunch with a bigger party (7). The atmosphere is wild and very eclectic. We had a reservation but still had to wait 20 minutes. Then, the server was all over the place. Every cocktail he served was spilled all over the glass and table, water was splashed on the table with each pour, and for the coffee, I can only describe it as being poured aggressively. Food went both ways. My wife's crab cakes were quite good, while my hash was pretty bland. Comments around the table were similar, with one dish being good and the other just fine. My favorite part was the Marie Antoinette cocktail. That was tasty! Everything else I could take or leave.

cafes.name: Alley Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 31 N Saginaw St, Pontiac, MI 48342, USA

text.text: Such a cool place. The bar tender was the best, super friendly and fun. The crab cakes were the best I‚Äôve had in Michigan! The cocktails were strong but yummy! The bar tender gave us a tour of the place and was telling us how the basement is haunted. This place is connected to a coffee shop that‚Äôs open during the day which is also good and worth trying. You can have a small event here too.
The food is fantastic, the staff is great and the music was even better!! Highly recommend 5/5. We will be back!

Went to a private event here in the lower level, couldn‚Äôt have had a better experience. The space is perfect and inviting, the food was excellent, and had a very nice selection of drinks with an excellent bartender. The owners and workers care about your time here, definitely check it out!

cafes.name: Karma Kat Cafe & Rescue
cafes.address: 612 E Broadway St, Mt Pleasant, MI 48858, USA

text.text: The most amazing rescue. Social beautiful cats looking for their forever homes. This allows you to see personality, and fall in love. I cannot recommend this place enough. It's even a great stop in just in town and looking for an activity. If you live cats...you will LOVE this place!!!!!!

Ever wanted to be surrounded by lots of loving kitties all at once? This is the place to be. Great volunteer experience too - you get to hang with the kitties for free after and they love attention when you first get there.

Visiting this cat cafe has been an incredibly heartwarming experience. Mystie and her team of volunteers are true heroes. Their dedication to rescuing and caring for cats is extraordinary. They provide a safe and loving environment, giving these cats a second chance at life.
The cafe itself is cozy and welcoming. You can feel the love and care that goes into every aspect of the cafe, from the cleanliness to the well-being of the cats.

It's baffling to see any negative reviews. Those individuals clearly don‚Äôt understand how cats are or the effort it takes to run such a compassionate business. Mystie and her team go above and beyond, not just in caring for the cats, but also in educating the public about cat care and adoption.

If you're looking for a place to donate or visit, this cat cafe should be at the top of your list. The work they do is inspiring, and every visit helps support their mission. :)
